EndingCards.Title: Frogman, The Forgotten
EndingCards.Card: Frogman promptly left after the final battle. He returned to his old town, only to be killed by monsters soon after.

EndingCards.Title: Frogman, Collaborator
EndingCards.Card: Frogman joined forces with Torment against humanity. He wasn't very useful to Torment, however, and died soon after.

EndingCards.Title: Frogman, Perfect Pawn
EndingCards.Card: Frogman was chosen by Fashima to be Torment's new champion, as the perfect mix of ambition and idiocy.

EndingCards.Title: Firbell, Lost Princess
EndingCards.Card: Firbell searched far and wide for her beloved Irenhold. She eventually lost touch with the world, and slowly wasted away.

EndingCards.Title: Firbell, Last Princess
EndingCards.Card: Firbell was assassinated along with the rest of Irenhold's royal family, which led to the kingdom's collapse.

EndingCards.Title: Kresla, Revived Legend
EndingCards.Card: Kresla brought her discoveries back to Bromzing, and lead the new research on Torment's magic, to disastrous results.

EndingCards.Title: Kresla, Curious Corpse
EndingCards.Card: Kresla found a Magma Emblem with her assistant, a Guard agent. She killed herself before he could take it.

EndingCards.Title: Xirveros, Forever Mad
EndingCards.Card: Torment took over Xirveros' mind and turned him into their new champion. He terrorised humanity with mad glee.

EndingCards.Title: Xirveros, Ghost Story
EndingCards.Card: Xirveros' sudden disappearance alarmed Kirsong and he decided to hide the other Emblem. It was recovered years later.

EndingCards.Title: Xeplogi, Failed Duke
EndingCards.Card: Xeplogi returned to his homeland and tried to warn the populace of Torment's return. Nobody listened.

EndingCards.Title: Xeplogi, Duke of Greed
EndingCards.Card: Xeplogi heard rumours of magic in his duchy and wanted it for himself. Memerian killed him when he grabbed an Emblem.

EndingCards.Title: Memerian, Lone Hermit
EndingCards.Card: Memerian left shortly after the battle to a secluded forest. She was never heard from again.

EndingCards.Title: Memerian, Evil Witch
EndingCards.Card: Memerian managed to make a few Emblems before Duke Xeplogi found her. She killed him, but his guards killed her in turn.

EndingCards.Title: Alfred, The Avenger
EndingCards.Card: Alfred finally fulfilled his dying wish - destroying the Guards. Soon after, he joined the fight against Torment.

EndingCards.Title: Alfred, Eternal Rebel
EndingCards.Card: Alfred failed to protect his Boss from Fashima's wrath, but managed to retrieve an Emblem before Fashima killed him too.

EndingCards.Title: Fashima, Doombringer
EndingCards.Card: Torment kept Fashima chained, powerless and in eternal pain, forcing her to watch as humanity burned around her.

EndingCards.Title: Fashima, World Saviour
EndingCards.Card: Fashima left the underground and set out to explore the world, free at last from all who had chained her.

EndingCards.Title: Werse, The Last Magus
EndingCards.Card: Werse managed to rescue a few Guards from the Fortress. They founded a safe haven for survivors, far from Torment.

EndingCards.Title: Werse, The Last Magus
EndingCards.Card: Werse was devestated after Fashima's victory. Eventually, they left the Fortress and wrote several novels about it.

EndingCards.Title: Torment, Revived God
EndingCards.Card: Torment immediately set out to take over humanity again, using their endless power and unlimited monster hordes.

EndingCards.Title: Lan, The Very Best
EndingCards.Card: Lan was surprised when all the Guards vanished suddenly. He shrugged it off, however, and became the best fisher ever.
